		<hr size="1">I agree, the PvP should be geared more towards actual battle scenarios, in keeping with the "rpg" flavor of the game.  Perhaps a point system (like ldon) or even xp awarded for killing a player, where the amount of the reward is reflective of the lvl/class/race/gear of the player? </P><P>Perhaps also faction hits (there are some now where if you kill enough humans/elves the guards in Qeynos will KOS you, for example) but perhaps it could be worked into the new "consider tool" where if you target a guy who's been killing elves for a living and you are an elf, the consider tool will inform you (much like with a mob) that this char is "ready to attack" instead of "indifferent". Granted, PKers would now be much more identifiable, but wouldn't that make sense in the roleplaying game? </P><P> For example, no xp/points should be rewarded to a player with superior gear/weps who kills a lvl 6 naked char! But if that naked char somehow manages to kill the superior geared player (lol probably wouldnt happen but for the sake of argument...) he would be awarded points/xp reflective of this accomplishment.</P><P>I think PvP could be vastly improved to make it a more involved part of the EQ experience, instead of a way for a certain few to make annoyances of themselves by cutting swathes of destruction through noob zones...</P><P>Anyways, those are my thoughts of the day =) I am sure not all will agree, but please discuss if you have other ideas or if you think this type of thing would be a worthwhile change to the game?<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
